  "description": "Construction of infill side extension at ground, first and second floor level of both nos. 64 and 65; alterations of the roofs of each property, raising roof ridge by 550mm while retaining current slope profile, in order to create accommodation at loft level, currently eaves storage; re-roofing with natural Welsh slate and lead flashing; to rear roof slope are proposed flush-fitting conservation velux windows, 3 for each house in alignment to fenestration pattern below; demolition of existing rear conservatory at no. 66 South Edwardes Square and erection of a unified single-storey ground floor extensions for both nos. 65 and 66, forming an enlarged reception and dining space, built in matching brickwork to a height of 2.8m and projecting 1.5m; laying of a non-visible green roof atop rear ground floor extension of nos. 65-66 (15m2) as well as on flat roof component of combined roofs of nos 63-66 (60m2); addition of water butts for rainwater harvesting to each house; improvements to architectural detailing namely, cleaning and repointing of elevation brickwork; extending plaster render banding on front elevation; addition of a cornice dressing and terracotta chimney pots to front chimney stacks; and formation of openings between nos. 65-66 amalgamating the houses to form reconfigured dwelling house.",
